&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Appspace:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At Appspace, we’re passionate about creating better work experiences for people everywhere, and we’re looking for people that feel the same way. Our global office locations and flexible work culture help you work wherever and however you’re at your best. Plus, we take the time to help you enjoy your work, build lasting connections, and grow your role. Join the Appspace team and be a part of a culture that’s helping people everywhere love where they work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role as a Enterprise Account Executive:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Enterprise Account Executives are dynamic, engaging, and entrepreneurial. They are responsible for driving strategy, planning, and executing sales to acquire targeted accounts, maximize assigned customer revenue, and engage with partners to grow overall revenue. By working closely with our strategic partners and channel community, or directly selling to customers, the AE will drive revenue growth through ongoing pipeline development and deal-winning activities. The successful candidate should be comfortable in customer, prospect and partner-facing roles and possess strong presentation skills, technical acumen, and the drive to win.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Day in the Life of a Enterprise Account Executive:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take a leadership role driving Appspace sales for your assigned territory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Target accounts to acquire as new Appspace customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Find new opportunities and grow business within your assigned customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the go-to expert on Appspace in a collaborative sales approach with strategic technology and channel partners - finding, winning and delivering business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and execute on an innovative business plan with our strategic partners and channel community to meet and exceed customer needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present and demonstrate the Appspace story and platform in early sales stages and coordinate additional resources as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with cross-functional resources from Engineering, Marketing, IT, Legal, Security and others as needed to drive Appspace sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow and convert pipeline from multiple sources, establishing reference customers in the process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately forecast pipeline development and report on opportunities within your assigned territory to deliver sales results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate with peers, partners, and customers using a win/win philosophy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Appspace at partner meetings, trade shows, events, and conferences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Need:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years experience in a sales and/or business development role in an information Technology capacity (Hardware, Software, Networking, etc.) with SaaS selling experience strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree; Business and/or Computer Science/IT preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial thinker; aggressive, energetic, self-starter with an established skillset in solution and relationship sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven history of performance in developing and maintaining strong prospect, partner, and customer relationships including confidence in presenting to senior levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in team selling approach, comfortable applying business acumen and financial expertise to identify and qualify opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in sales strategies including discovery, deal qualification, negotiation, close&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience and proficient user of Salesforce or other enterprise-level CRM systems&lt;/li&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Appspace:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At Appspace, we’re passionate about creating better work experiences for people everywhere, and we’re looking for people that feel the same way. Our global office locations and flexible work culture help you work wherever and however you’re at your best. Plus, we take the time to help you enjoy your work, build lasting connections, and grow your role. Join the Appspace team and be a part of a culture that’s helping people everywhere love where they work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role as an Implementation Specialist:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a detail-oriented implementation professional with deep expertise in intranet technology, internal communications platforms, and workplace management solutions? Do you thrive on guiding customers through complex migrations and new deployments while keeping the employee experience front and center? Appspace is looking for an Implementation Specialist to join the Appspace Professional Services team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will own the end-to-end implementation of Appspace Intranet and Internal Communications solutions for new customers, while also leading platform migrations from Sharepoint and Igloo to Appspace. Rounding out your portfolio, you will support Workplace Management implementations – including space reservation, digital signage, and related workplace experience products – on a smaller portion of your engagements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is structured as 80% Intranet and Internal Communications implementations and 20% Workplace Management projects, giving you a primary domain of deep expertise while keeping your skills broad across the full Appspace platform.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Day in the Life of an Implementation Specialist:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Intranet Implementation &amp;amp; Onboarding&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver Appspace Intranet configurations for new and existing customers, delivering configuration, content setup, and preparation for go-live.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary implementation resource, setting clear expectations with internal teams to communicate to customers, managing timelines, and maintaining strong communication with the organization throughout each engagement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and validate Appspace Intranet environments to meet each customer&#39;s specific structural, design, and content requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;When required, deliver tailored onboarding sessions and training to customer administrators and content managers, enabling self-sufficiency post-launch.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;When required, consult on intranet best practices including information architecture, content governance, navigation design, and user experience to set customers up for long-term success.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal Communications Implementation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement Appspace Internal Communications features including news feeds, announcements, targeted content channels, and employee engagement tools.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise on internal communications strategy – helping to structure content hierarchies, define publishing workflows, and reach the right audiences effectively.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure content distribution settings, audience targeting, and governance controls aligned to each customer&#39;s communications team structure and approval processes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support customers in migrating existing internal communications content and structures into the Appspace platform, ensuring continuity of employee experience.&amp;nbsp;&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Appspace:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At Appspace, we’re passionate about creating better work experiences for people everywhere, and we’re looking for people that feel the same way. Our global office locations and flexible work culture help you work wherever and however you’re at your best. Plus, we take the time to help you enjoy your work, build lasting connections, and grow your role. Join the Appspace team and be a part of a culture that’s helping people everywhere love where they work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role as a Performance Test Lead:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Performance Test Lead, you will be responsible for building and owning Appspace&#39;s performance engineering capability from the ground up. This is a foundational role — you will define the strategy, select the toolchain, establish the first baselines across our product suite, and integrate performance gates directly into our CI/CD pipeline. You will serve as the technical authority on all performance decisions, ensuring that every service boundary in Appspace&#39;s platform is covered by a measurable, enforceable performance contract. As we scale our AI-driven development lifecycle (AIDLC), you will also ensure that AI-generated code meets the same performance standards as human-written code — making automation the enforcer of quality, not a bypass of it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Day in the Life of a Performance Test Lead:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end performance testing strategy across all Appspace product lines — Digital Signage, Space Reservation, Visitor Management, and Intranet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and maintain a performance testing framework using k6 (primary) and Locust, with a baseline artifact store in Google Cloud Storage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish performance baselines for critical user journeys and service boundaries, starting with Signage as the highest-traffic product line.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate automated performance gates into the CI/CD pipeline, ensuring regressions are caught before they reach production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI and AI tools throughout the entire test lifecycle—from generating test cases, optimizing test execution schedules, to autonomously monitoring test results and identifying performance degradation patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and enforce performance SLAs — including p95 latency targets, throughput thresholds, and error rate limits — across all product domains.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with AI Delivery Leads in each product squad to ensure that AI-generated code touching service boundaries triggers automated load test candidates in the pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Co-author performance test plans with domain engineers across Signage, Space+Visitor, Intranet, and Core Platform squads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and operate regression detection alerting, feeding results into the AIDLC metrics framework and engineering leadership dashboards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion performance engineering best practices across globally distributed engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate performance posture, test coverage progress, and regression trends accurately and regularly to engineering leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow the function over time — mentoring a Phase 2 AI QE / Performance Engineer sourced from the internal QA retraining programme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or equivalent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 7 years of experience with at least 4 years specializing in performance engineering roles focused on end-to-end system performance in high-scale, multi-tenant, SaaS applications, including perf

